1. Hard Drives can give a heat (bad sectors // no time to write // during backups) right now not so huge problem due SSD.
2. Master Slave Replication things (Primary Keys (Long, Int, UUID), scaling data sync).
3. Deadlocks on huge request amount.
4. Cache outage.
5. Temporary tables.
6. Complex Joins.
7. Huge indexes.
8. Wrong field data types.